<p><b>Free-market environmentalism</b> is a position that argues that the <a href="/wiki/Free_market" title="Free market">free market</a>, <a href="/wiki/Property_rights" title="Property rights" class="mw-redirect">property rights</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Tort" title="Tort">tort</a> law provide the best tools to preserve the health and sustainability of the <a href="/wiki/Natural_environment" title="Natural environment">environment</a>. This is in contrast to the most common modern approach of proactive environmental <a href="/wiki/Legislation" title="Legislation">legislation</a>.</p>
