<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHansmann.2C_H._.26_Kraakman.2C_R.1991">Hansmann, H. &amp; Kraakman, R. (1991). "Toward unlimited shareholder liability for corporate torts". <i>Yale Law Review</i> <b>100</b>: 1879. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F796812" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F796812" rel="nofollow">10.2307/796812</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Toward+unlimited+shareholder+liability+for+corporate+torts&amp;rft.jtitle=Yale+Law+Review&amp;rft.aulast=Hansmann%2C+H.+%26+Kraakman%2C+R.&amp;rft.au=Hansmann%2C+H.+%26+Kraakman%2C+R.&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.volume=100&amp;rft.pages=1879&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.2307%2F796812&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Free-market_environmentalism"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Stroup, Richard L. (2003) <i>Eco-nomics: What Everyone Should Know About Economics and the Environment</i> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1930865449" class="internal">ISBN 1-930865-44-9</a></li>
<li>Krugman, Paul (1999) <i><a href="http://www.slate.com/id/1919/" class="external text" title="http://www.slate.com/id/1919/" rel="nofollow">Earth in the balance sheet: economists go for the green</a></i> and <i>Taxes and traffic jams</i> reprinted in <i>The Accidental Theorist</i> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0140286861" class="internal">ISBN 0-14-028686-1</a></li>
<li>Ridley, M &amp; Low, B S (1993) <i><a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/environ/selfish.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/environ/selfish.htm" rel="nofollow">Can selfishness save the environment?</a></i>, <i>The Atlantic Monthly</i> vol. 272, pp. 76-86</li>
<li>Simon, Julian (1998) <i>The Ultimate Resource 2</i> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691003815" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-00381-5</a></li>
<li><a href="http://commonsblog.org/free_reading.php" class="external text" title="http://commonsblog.org/free_reading.php" rel="nofollow">free-market Environmentalism Bibliography</a> on The Commons Blog</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Free-market_environmentalism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cato.org/pubs/journal/cj2n1/cj2n1-2.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.cato.org/pubs/journal/cj2n1/cj2n1-2.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Law, Property Rights, and Air Pollution,"</a> <small>1.8 MB PDF</small> Murray N. Rothbard, <i>Cato Journal</i>, Vol. 2, No. 1 (Spring 1982), pp. 55-100.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cato.org/pubs/journal/cj1n2-1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cato.org/pubs/journal/cj1n2-1.html" rel="nofollow">"Resolving the Tragedy of the Commons by Creating Private Property Rights in Wildlife,"</a> Robert J. Smith, <i>Cato Journal</i>, Vol. 1, No. 2 (Fall 1981), pp. 439-468.</li>
<li><a href="http://commonsblog.org/free_reading.php" class="external text" title="http://commonsblog.org/free_reading.php" rel="nofollow">"Free-Market Environmentalism Reading List,"</a> The Commons Blog: Markets Protecting the Environment.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc/EnvironmentalismFreeMarket.html" class="external text" title="http://www.econlib.org/library/Enc/EnvironmentalismFreeMarket.html" rel="nofollow">"Environmentalism, Free-Market,"</a> Richard L. Stroup, The Concise Encyclopedia of Economics: Library of Economics and Liberty</li>
<li><a href="http://www.independent.org/pdf/tir/tir_10_1_2_pennington.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.independent.org/pdf/tir/tir_10_1_2_pennington.pdf" rel="nofollow">A Hayekian Defense of Free-Market Environmentalism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.social-ecology.org/article.php?story=20031202111003557" class="external text" title="http://www.social-ecology.org/article.php?story=20031202111003557" rel="nofollow">Trading Away the Earth: Pollution Credits and the Perils of "Free Market Environmentalism"</a></li>
<li><a href="http://treesinstead.com" class="external text" title="http://treesinstead.com" rel="nofollow">The sale of trees for profit, Trees Instead</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ti.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.ti.org/" rel="nofollow">The Thoreau Institute - a pro-free market environmentalism group</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nature.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.nature.org/" rel="nofollow">The Nature Conservancy</a> has posted much information on <a href="http://nature.org/aboutus/howwework/conservationmethods/privatelands/conservationeasements/" class="external text" title="http://nature.org/aboutus/howwework/conservationmethods/privatelands/conservationeasements/" rel="nofollow">conservation easements</a> and other tools pertaining to free-market environmentalism</li>
<li><a href="http://www.anthonares.net/2005/06/fighting-global-warming-free-market.html" class="external text" title="http://www.anthonares.net/2005/06/fighting-global-warming-free-market.html" rel="nofollow">Fighting Global Warming–Free Market Style</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ecoworld.com/blog/2007/03/26/supply-side-environmentalism/" class="external text" title="http://www.ecoworld.com/blog/2007/03/26/supply-side-environmentalism/" rel="nofollow">Supply Side Environmentalism: EcoWorld</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aere.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.aere.org/" rel="nofollow">Association of Environmental and Resource Economists</a> (AERE).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journaldescription.cws_home/622870/description#description" class="external text" title="http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journaldescription.cws_home/622870/description#description" rel="nofollow">- JEEM: Journal of Environmental Economics and Management</a> (AERE's official "technical" journal).</li>
<li><a href="http://reep.oxfordjournals.org/" class="external text" title="http://reep.oxfordjournals.org/" rel="nofollow">- REEP: Review of Environmental Economics and Policy</a> (AERE's official "accessible" journal).</li>
</ul>
